Package org.jungrapht.visualization.layout.algorithms

Class SpringLayoutAlgorithm<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jungrapht.visualization.layout.algorithms.AbstractIterativeLayoutAlgorithm<V>
      • org.jungrapht.visualization.layout.algorithms.SpringLayoutAlgorithm<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IterativeLayoutAlgorithm<V>, LayoutAlgorithm<V>, IterativeContext
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DAGLayoutAlgorithm
    public class SpringLayoutAlgorithm<V>
extends AbstractIterativeLayoutAlgorithm<V>
implements IterativeContext
    The SpringLayout package represents a visualization of a set of vertices. The SpringLayout, which is initialized with a Graph, assigns X/Y locations to each vertex. When called step() , the SpringLayout moves the visualization forward one step.
    Author:
    Danyel Fisher, Joshua O'Madadhain, Tom Nelson
